-1 SACRIFICE SAC SACCING DESTROY~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|            SACRIFICE DESTROY                                        |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Destroy <Item>
        Sacrifice <Item> <Optional Deity>

In Avendar, you can remove an item from the game by using the DESTROY or the SACRIFICE command.

DESTROY will destroy an item completely.

SACRIFICE sacrifices an item to a specific deity.

Generally speaking, a sacrifice allows you the chance
to obtain a reward from your deity, often dependent on
the power of the item sacrificed.

Be warned, however, that not all deities are pleased with
inappropriate or unworthy sacrifices, or do not wish to
be disturbed at all. Sacrifices to these deities could
conceivably lead to a dire fate!

You may specify no deity, and receive a chance at
generic (albeit less potent) benefits with your sacrifice.
(Note: this feature will be implemented shortly)

Currently, you may sacrifice items to Jolinn or Enaerai. (More deities
coming very shortly.)

~
-1 RYSTAIA PEGASUS CHOSEN FREEDOM JOY PASSION CASHMEREWHORE~

Rystaia is a ch'taren god, who helped guild the them
to Avendar in ancient times passed. She stands for the
principles of Joy, Freedom, and Passion, and welcomes worship
from any whose heart leads them to her temples, though
predominantly her followers are good, and of chaotic ethoi.

The followers of Rystaia are known as the Chosen, and
are branded with either the Alabaster Pegasus, Soaring
Pegasus, or for the most dedicated, the Pegasus with
Wings of Light.

FREEDOM
=======
The most important of Rystaia's doctrines is that of
freedom, the ability to live in accordance with one's
heart. Those that are truly free are not enslaved by
their desires, and are untouched by the binding
temptations of greed, anger, or hate.
When one is truly free, only the pure intentions
of the heart will guide thee.

Evil taints and shackles the soul, rendering all who
walk in the darkness enslaved by their petty and cruel
ways. It is the calling of the Chosen of Rystaia
to free all those trapped by their physical and
mental bonds, and to destroy those that would seek
to enslave their fellow creatures. This is done not
with hatred, but with the goal of releasing those of
dark intentions from the prison their hearts have
created. The bonds of fear and darkness are stronger
than steel, and often the only release from them
can be found in the afterlife.

PASSION
=======
When one is free from the grasp of the tempations of
the darkness, one can begin to follow their heart.
That which follows, Passion, comes most naturally.
The Chosen, those that are passionate in life, give
themselves entirely to the moment, never holding back.
To truly embody this ideal, one must never shy from
life, and instead commit one's self fully to that
which they know to be Good.

JOY
===
The third and final principle of the Chosen, Joy, is
that which truly makes life worth living. Those who
truly embody this trait are able to find happiness,
no matter how bleak their outlook may be. To have the
wisdom to appreciate a rose in a battlefield is
difficult, but in the end one of the most precious
gifts of all.

~
-1 Rveyelhi 'Black Staff'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|             Rveyelhi                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Rveyelhi, a once-mortal shuddeni Guardian, is a servitor
deity of Iandir. He currently oversees the house of
Guardian in Iandir's stead while the greater deity
tends to other planes and worlds.  

A brutally efficient guardsman in mortality, Rveyelhi
endorses a similarly strict manner of dealing with
criminals.  Followers of Rveyelhi believe that those
who would break the law are little more than rabid
animals clawing at the tapestry of civilization. These
beasts are to be put down, lest their scratching
unweave it.  Law breakers, as well as anyone else who
would bring chaos to the world, are to be dealt with
by any means within the bounds of law and with no mercy.
  
Followers of Rveyelhi found worthy are branded with the 
Sigil of the Black Staff.
  
Also see: Help GUARDIAN, Help IANDIR and Help LAW.
~

-1 Enaerai 'Lady of Balance' 'Lady balance' 'Eye of Enaerai'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       Enaerai, Lady of Balance                                      |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

    Enaerai is among the deities who came to Avendar after the three great
powers had wrought the world.  Finding the balance and harmony of their
creation to be precious, and believing powers of fate to be in play that
supersede even the creators, she works to maintain the balance among the
many conflicting forces in the world.  Her efforts take place primarily in
the immortal realms, and she does not often directly interact with mortals. 

    In times past, dedicants to Enaerai, whose hearts were true in balance and
neutrality, organized themselves into the Order of the Knights of Enaerai.
The knighthood they founded continues, working in Enaerai's name by her
blessing, to preserve the balance among mortals.

See also: Help KNIGHTS OF ENAERAI
~

-1 'Knights of Enaerai' 'Knight Enaerai' 'The Knights of Enaerai' 'Order of Enaerai' 'The Knights of Enaerai' ~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|  The Knights of Enaerai                                             |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The Order of the Knights of Enaerai

The Knights of Enaerai seek to uphold the balance in Avendar.  By persuasion
or by force, and acting as a unified military body, the Knights are ever
vigilant that no extreme influence disrupts the equilibrium and natural
balance as created when the three great powers first brought Avendar into
being.  

The Knights revere Enaerai, who is held as their guiding deity of balance,
though no active worship is required throughout the Order.  They also
observe Mettenday, the first calendar day of every month on the standard
Avendarian calendar, as a day of rest, recuperation, and assembly.  No
efforts to actively enforce balance are made by the Knights on Mettenday. 
The Knights are based in the city of Earendam, in a compound adjunct to the
Temple of Enaerai.  

REQUIREMENTS OF KNIGHTHOOD

Adventurers who are neutral in both alignment and ethos may become Knights
of Enaerai.  However, scholars who practice the greater spells of spirit or
void, and templars of those spheres, may not seek entrance to the
Knighthood.  To join the Knights of Enaerai, seek out members of the order
and petition them for entrance.  Knights may be recognized by the symbol of
Enaerai--the eye within a triangle.  

THE OFFICES OF KNIGHTHOOD

The organization of the Knighthood is straightforward, run with the
efficiency and manner one would expect of a military order.  Knights heed
the directions of their superiors without question, sacrificing life and
even soul to the cause.  

The Knight Lord leads the Knights.  He or she is the highest officer and
supreme commander of the Knights, maintaining the order of the knighthood
and directing them in actions to right the balance.  

There are up to three captains of the Knights, who vote for the new Lord
should the office be absent.  Each is also given the leadership of the Mett,
Idris, or Ilthar divisions of the Knights.  

The Captain of Mett is charged with subterfuge, spying, scouting, and
providing necessary reconnaissance, as well as leading the rogue component
and other miscellaneous forces of the Knight body.  

The Captain of Idris pools and compiles knowledge regarding adventurers in
the land and their effects on the balance, and the balance between houses,
as well as leading the magical or scholarly forces of the Knight body.  

The Captain of Ilthar is charged with being the second, under the Knight
Lord, to direct in battle, to administer punishment of final death to
renegade Knights who have broaken their oaths of Knighthood, and to lead the
warrior forces of the Knight body.

~

-1 ACCOUNTS ACCOUNT 'NO ACCOUNTING FOR TASTE'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|               Accounts                                              |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Avendar features an ACCOUNT system for its players.

Basically, this means that rather than using individual characters,
a player has the option of creating an account to manage his or
her characters from, and to establish a reputation with.

Players create, or add new characters to an existing account,
only during character creation, AND AT NO OTHER TIME.

This means: If you want a character to be a part of your account,
this must be done at creation.


Your account's name is the name of the first character you ever
create with an account.

To use your account, simply log in with your account's name and
password.

If you are playing from a banned site, you will require an account
to play.

Each player is allowed precisely (1) account. Attempting to create
multiple accounts is considered a violation of the rules, and doing
so with the purpose of creating multiple identities for yourself is
a bannable offense. 

Accounts are voluntary, but people who maintain an account can
establish a reputation with the mortals for good roleplaying, and
will be rewarded accordingly.

We highly encourage you to play your characters from an account,
as it allows immortals to target and reward good roleplayers.
Expect more benefits from accounts as time goes on.


See also: Help ACCTPWD, Help ACCOUNT RULES
~
