-1 'DEMON SUMMON' 'DEMON SUMMONING' 'LESSER DEMON SUMMON' 'GREATER DEMON SUMMON' 'GREATER DEMON'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|          Demon Summon                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Lesser Demon Summon'
        Cast 'Demon Summon'
        Cast 'Greater Demon Summon'

Demonic conjuration is the power which defines the discipline of
void magic. Every void scholar who is more than a dabbler in the Art
learns how to conjure at least a few lesser demons, and the most
powerful scholars can bring forth demon lords so powerful that even
kings tremble at their passing.

Of course, binding the deceptive, treacherous, and willful denizens
of the Void is not a trivial or even straightforward task. Each and
every demon is bound by a characteristic inscription, written
with a particular material, conjured with one of the three rituals,
and has a specific price.

Inscriptions (See help INSCRIBE) are diabolical symbols which void
scholars must acquire and burn into their soul. Once learned, the void
scholar may INSCRIBE the symbol in a location, in preparation for
summoning a demon.

Materials (see help MATERIALS) are what symbols are inscribed in.
They are typically symbolic in nature, and vary greatly.

The rituals are the three spells of demon summoning. More powerful
demons are accessed through increasingly powerful spells, but a given
demon will only respond to a particular ritual (i.e., if lesser demon summon produces a certain demon in conjunction with a given symbol and material, it is not the case that greater demon summoning would produce the same demon.)

Finally, every demon will demand a price of the caster. The more
powerful the demon, generally, the more potent the price. The wise
scholar is encouraged to determine what the price might be before
summoning a demon, as the failure to be may be very dire indeed.

So, to summarize: A given demon is summoned by the conjunction of:
-A mystical symbol
-A material in which the symbol will be inscribed
-A particular ritual (lesser, normal, or greater demon summon)

Void scholars who study and are well-traveled will find clues as to
what demons require in the way of prices, symbols, materials, and
rituals. 

WARNING: It is not advised that void scholars randomly experiment
with given combinations of material, symbol, and ritual -- there
can be extremely dire consequences to certain conjunctions!
~

