-1 INSCRIBE SYMBOLS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|            Inscribe                                                 |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Inscribe <Mystical Figure> <Material>
        Inscribe

Both void templars and scholars can inscribe mystic figures in order
to aid them in the practice of their craft. Certain spells require 
these mystical figures be present, and certain materials are needed
to inscribe them. 

There are certain basic symbols, which every void scholar and templar
knows:

Figure Type:                              * Material Needed:

Circle of Protection                        Silver dust

Trigon of Binding                           Charcoal

Pentagram of Summoning                      Powdered Bone

(These materials are for the void templar class, who have limited
use of symbols.)

Circles of Protection provide resistance to summoning and other 
extraworldly forms of transportation.

Trigons of binding are used in rituals to bind demons into items.

Penatagrams of summoning are used for the basic summoning ritual.


There are other, more complicated symbols in addition to these,
which void scholars use in the summoning and binding of demons.
These symbols are not available to starting void scholars, and must
be found in Avendar, often requiring that the void scholar study
the symbols.

Once learned, scholars can access which symbols they know through
the use of the inscribe command without an argument.

Different demons are summoned by different symbols, so knowing
a wide variety of symbols ensures a diversity of options to
the void scholar.

The materials for mystic figures are typically available in larger
towns, either from guildmasters or magic shops. Certain rarer
ingredients will require more effort to find (rare herbs, etc.)

See also:

Help ERASE, SYMBOLS, DEMON SUMMON, MATERIAL

~
-1 MATERIAL MATERIALS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|           Materials                                                 |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Materials are the ingredients scholars and templars use in
inscribing mystical symbols. Common materials are generally
available in guilds or apothecaries, while other, more exotic
materials might require more effort.

Common ingredients include charcoal, powdered bone, silver dust, or salt.

Less common ingredients may include the blood of various creatures
(including the caster!), for which a glass vial is required and an
exsanguination may be required.

See also:

Help INSCRIBE, DEMON SUMMON, SYMBOLS, EXSANGUINATE, BLEED, DEBONE

