-1 SYTHRAK 'SAURIAN SEPT' SAURIAN SEPT~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|               Sythrak                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The srryn followers of Sythrak, known to mortals as the Saurian Sept,
walk the land with but one purpose, to serve and fear the immortal word 
of their god.  Destruction and havoc come in their wake, as the strong
overwhelm all who show signs of weakness.  Brute strength has many uses 
to break the will of the weak may be more useful than spilling blood, 
as every srryn overlord enjoys his warmblood slaves.  Exhibiting the 
strength and brutality of their srryn elders in every form, the Sept 
shun weakness, knowing that by giving in to their own weakness makes 
them no more superior than the warmblood swine that that exists around 
them.  This brutality does not end among the ranks of the Sept.  The 
children of Sythrak constantly fight amongst themselves, rending one 
another to prove their strength to their immortal Lord, and perhaps 
gain his favor.  Brandings are passed among the ranks of the Sept like 
trophies, to be gained only through battle and bloodshed. Because of 
these brutal guidelines, honor holds no place in the Sept -- only 
animal instinct.

Often, the Sept are used as tools of Sythrak to extend his reach over 
the mortal realm, serving as assassins or messengers for their lord. 
Failure at these tasks has grave consequences. One who fails to obey 
their Lord or complete these tasks fully are to be punished by Sythrak 
himself.  Failure is weakness, and weakness is not tolerated within the 
ranks of the Sept. While ancient texts state it can only be srryn that 
speak to Sythrak on the matter of the Sept, rules can be bent to 
include warmblood toys.  Warmbloods that wish to serve Sythrak and his
 Sept are kept as slaves, used in battles and sacrificed as he wishes. 
Such servants of the Sept are regarded as the lowest form of life, and 
are to be kept as pets of the Srryn Overlord himself. Those that seek 
an audience with Sythrak should address a note to him directly, 
explaining why they deem themselves fit to enter the ranks of the
Saurian Sept.
~

