-1 EDIT EDITOR~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|           Editor                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Note Edit
        Desc Edit
        Background Edit 

An editor exists for editing the main body of your notes, descriptions,
and backgrounds.

Once you activate the editor, you will be given a prompt that looks 
like this:

>

At the prompt, you can type whatever text you want to add to your 
note or description. 

To enter editor commands, you must go to a newline. All editor 
commands are prefaced by a ".", with the exception of "@". The
commands are as follows:

.c Clear all text from the editor (Delete everything)
.s Show everything written so far, as it will appear.
.h Get help on editor commands.
.f Format your text (No more messy notes or descriptions!)
@  Leave the editor

WARNING: While in the editor, you can input no mud commands to
your character. This puts you at some risk to attack if you are
unprepared, so be mindful of the possibilities.

NOTE: If you're using the zMUD client, you may need to disable
"." as your movement character before using the editor.  Read
help ZMUD for details.

~

-1 ZMUD~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|         zMUD                                                        |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

In order to use the string editor with the zMUD client, you may be
required to disable "." as the movement character in order to use
the special editor commands.  To accomplish this, do the following:

- Pull down the View menu, and select Preferences
- Click on Special Characters
- Make sure the Enabled checkbox beside the "." Movement Character
  option is unchecked.

The above instructions are for the newest version of zMUD (6.16), but
similar steps can be used in older versions, with minor changes.

~

-1 BACKGROUND BG~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|         Background                                                  |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The BACKGROUND command allows a character to describe their 
background. 

Your background describes your character's past -- and it should 
include whatever you know about your own past, and what a god would
know about you and your history.

The background is meant to have a twofold use. Firstly, it allows
the immortals to ensure that everyone has a well-roleplayed 
character. Secondly, it allows the gods to understand your actions,
and allows for more subtle, and complicated roleplaying.

Only the immortals can read your background.

You are required to have a background by level 25. 

To enter your background, use the BACKGROUND command:

Background + :    Add a line to your background
Background - :    Remove a line from your background
Background clear: Clears your background completely
Background:       Shows your background
Background edit:  Edit your background completely*

* Be sure to read help EDIT before you use this command. 

See also: DESCRIPTION DESCRIPTION2 BACKGROUND2 ROLEPLAYING ROLEPLAYING2 EDITOR

~

