-1 'SHOOT'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|            Shoot                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Shoot <Target> <short/medium/long/barbed> <direction> 
              <aimed/normal/quick>                                          

The shoot skill is used to fire an arrow from a bow (which must be
held).  The target of shoot is any pc or npc visible to the person
shooting. There are four "basic" types of arrow, which are stored 
in your quiver. The four basic types are as follows:

Short: Base range of 2 
Medium: Base range of 3
Long: Base range of 4
Barbed: Base range of 2, barbed tip inflicts bleeding damage

The direction is the direction of your target. 

Three types of targeting can be used for the speed with which an arrow
is targeted:

Quick: Low accuracy, quick recovery
Normal: Average accuracy, normal recovery
Aimed: High accuracy, delay before firing 

In addition to firing arrows of the 'normal' types, there will be
occasionally arrows with various special (magical, etc.) properties
that can be fired.  To shoot these arrows, you must first load them
with the NOCK command [see help NOCK], and omit the argument of basic
arrow type.

In general, you can omit any of these arguments except for the target,
and the arrow fired will default to medium range (or the type you have
nocked)  and of normal firing time. Omitting a direction will attempt
to find the target automatically. In general, as long as the 'shoot'
command is first, the argument may be given in any order.

Finally, normal arrow types may be lit using the IGNITE [see help
IGNITE] command. Once ignited, the arrow will automatically fire when
the shoot command is used.

~


