-1 Iandir Crown 'Order of the Crown' Rigorist~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|          Iandir                                                     |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The Order of the Crown is a rigorist order of knights dedicated to the
principles of Iandir. Those who take the vows of the Crownbearer commit
themselves to a strict code of conduct, showing thereby their devotion
to Order and Law.
  Crownbearers may be good, neutral or evil, and may follow any House
affiliation, but must be lawful in ethos. A Crownbearer will usually
spend his life in pursuit of his own goals; however, he is expected to
bring Order to whatever that pursuit is, perhaps organizing a cause, or
leading a crusade.
  Followers of the Crown must comply with the following three principles:
1. Honesty. A Crownbearer must speak the absolute truth at all times, and
will never break his word.
2. Lawfulness. A Crownbearer lives in complete obedience to the Laws of
Avendar, and encourages others to do so as well.
3. Leadership. A Crownbearer recognizes that the essence of Order is the
organization of the forces of mankind, and applies the principles of
leadership to his endeavors.
  Iandir is currently in a state of semi-retirement, and is not taking
petitions for followers. Various lesser entities may be contacted for
membership in the Guardian house.
~





-1 ARKHURAL ARKHILRA SHIJARDU~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|          Arkhural                                                   |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The followers of Arkhural, Bringer of the Twilight, know that within 
this world, there is only one true source of power, the ability to
instill fear within the hearts of men.  All other aspects of power, the
aggregation of material wealth, the control of political authority,
stems from this. Those that are weak, and succumb to fear themselves, 
are little more than mindless cattle, and are to be treated as such.
  The Arkhilhra, known collectively as the Sect of the Shijardu, are 
deemed by Arkhural to be superior to the rest of humanity.  As such, 
they are unrestrained by both moral and secular law, although these 
may be utilized as tools to control the masses.  Forever seeking to 
increase their power, they hold little value to oaths or treaties, 
dismissing such things when it suits them.  Relentless in the pursuit
of their goals, they fear nothing, save the unsatiated bloodlust of 
their God.
  Those that seek the attention of the Lord of the Twilight should 
address a note to Arkhural.  Be forewarned, those that are found 
unworthy shall find that the Lord of the Twilight's time is not to
be trifled with.
~


