-1 SWORD SWORDS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|         Swords                                                      |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Swords are perhaps the most common of weapons in Avendar, known and
used by all professions save those of the scholars and druids. A sword
typically consists of a hilt (place to hold the sword), a crossbar,
and a blade. Blade lengths can be anywhere from 2' to 8', with the
very largest swords usable only by the giant races. Blades on swords
can either be one or two-sided, curved, straight, or even barbed to
inflict more lasting damage. Usually, a sword will inflict stabbing,
slashing, chopping, cutting, piercing, or cleaving damage. Swords have
traditionally been the weapon of choice for enchantments and other 
such magics. 

~
-1 DAGGER DAGGERS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|          Daggers                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Daggers are short bladed weapons, most commonly used by the rogueish
classes and those of scholarly bent who lack the time to learn more
complicated weapons. Dagger attacks usually involve quick thrusting,
piercing or stabbing attacks. Daggers offer very little in the way
of parrying, but their quick speed makes them hard to dodge.

~



-1 MACE MACES~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|          Maces                                                      |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

A mace is a blunt weapon, consisting of a block of metal attached to
a shaft, occasionally covered with spikes or edges to do more damage.
Maces usually attack with crushes or pounds, and are often employed by
barbarians, who are known for using their ferocious bludgeoning
attacks. Maces are also occasionally employed by footman, or the occasional 
scholar or templar.

~

-1 WHIP WHIPS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|         Whips                                                       |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

A whip consists of a flexible cord attached to a handle. The cord can
be made from any number of materials, but is most commonly leather.
Oft times, other sharp materials (such as glass or bits of metal) may
be embedded in the cord to inflict more damage. Whips are most commonly
used by gladiators (who are known for their exotic lashing and disarming
techniques), but also see some usage among some templars and
scholars.

~

-1 FLAIL FLAILS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|           Flails                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Flails are a rather uncommon class of weapon, used by and large by 
gladiators. Similar to a whip, a flail also consists of a handle and
a cord. Unlike the whip, however, the cord is not a single lash - it
instead links a series of objects together. These objects are typically
balls of metal, usually with with some sort of spikes or other sharp
protrusions designed to inflict damage.

~

-1 POLEARM POLEARMS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|             Polearms                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

A polearm is a blade of some form attached to a long (typically at
least 6' or more) pole. The attached blade may be akin to a sword,
axe, or more exotic design. Polearms are typically used to keep a foe
at a foe at a distance while striking with the blade.  Polearms are
favored by fighters, who often train in their use, both due to their,
reach, and their good parrying ability.
~
-1 STAFF~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|            Staff                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The staff is the most common two-handed weapon, most typically made 
from wood into a long pole. The staff is typically used to pound,
strike, or crush an opponent. Its long shaft allows for easy parrying
of blows, for which the staff is used primarily as a defensive weapon.
Due to its focus on defending against blows, the staff is often a
favorite weapon among scholars.

~
-1 SPEAR SPEARS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|            Spears                                                   |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

A spear is a long shaft topped by a sharpened tip. The shaft of a 
spear may also occasionally be barbed to inflict more damage. 
The attack of a spear is typically a pierce, stab, or impaling jab,
and the weapon is favored by gladiators, who often use the spear
to strike at vital organs. The spear is also occasionally used
by barbarians, and fighters, who are often trained in organized
phalanxes.  The parrying ability of the spear is second only to that
of the staff.
~
-1 AXE AXES~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|             Axes                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Axes are primarily offense weapons, most favored by the barbarians
for its sheer ferocity. Axes come in many varieties (both one handed
and two), but most all consist of a short shaft topped by either one
or two wedge-like blades, occasionally topped with a spike. Axes
usually slash, slice, cleave or chop in their attacks.

~




-1 HAND 'HAND TO HAND'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        Hand to Hand                                                 |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

The ability to use one's bare hands to inflict more damage than normal
is a skill known to adventurers in Avendar. The skill is automatically
attempted whenever no weapons are being used, and will cause these
blows to inflict more damage than normal.

~

-1 'FLOATING DISC' 'FLOATING DISK'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        Floating Disc                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Floating Disc'

The floating disc spell calls into existence an invisible disc of 
air. The disc will float by the caster for the duration of the spell,
on which items can be placed. The duration and weight allownace of
the disc depend on the level of the caster. Upon termination of the
spell, the disc will vanish, causing any items on it to tumble to the
ground. The spell requires that the caster be free of other floating
items to be successful.

~

-1 RECALL~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        Recall                                                       |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/


Syntax: RECALL (or /)

RECALL prays to the gods for miraculous transportation from where you are
back to the appropriate temple of your hometown.  

'/' is a synonym for RECALL.

RECALL costs half of your movement points.

RECALL doesn't work in certain god-forsaken rooms.  Characters afflicted by a
curse may not recall at all.

You may not recall from the middle of battle, or while your adrenaline
is gushing from combat.

Only characters of level less than 10 may use the automatic recall 
command. Other characters will have to find magical or other means 
to return themselves to recall to their hometown.

~



-1 KILL~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|         Kill                                                        |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Kill <Target>

The kill command has two functions. Firstly, it allows a player to 
initiate combat with a mobile.

The second use is in a fight with multiple participants. If a character
is being attacked by more than one person, he can switch who he targets
his blows toward by typing "kill <target>". Thusly, if someone is 
fighting a bear and a hen, to switch from striking at the bear to 
striking at the hen, type "kill hen". Kill cannot be used to draw in a
mob or person that is not already fighting if the character is already
otherwise engaged in a fight.

~

-1 HIDE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        Hide                                                         |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Hide

The hide command is used by rogues to seclude themselves within the
shadows. Hiding can only be attempted in civilized locales, and any
attempt to move while hidden will result in stepping out of the 
shadows unless the person hiding is currently sneaking. (See help
SNEAKING). The nature of hide is that a rogue attempting the skill
will not know whether he or she is successful - they must rely on
their ability to gauge the reactions of others to determine whether
or not they are succesfully hidden.

~

-1 CHAIN 'CHAIN LIGHTNING'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        Chain Lightning                                              |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Chain Lightning' <Target>

A stereotypically chaotic and ucontrolled spell of the school of air,
chain lightning is an offensive spell, designed to inflict electrical
damage on a foe. When the spell is cast, a long electrical arc hits
the victim, then bounces about the room, hitting every available 
target, not excluding the mage who cast the spell.

~


-1 LORE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        LORE                                                         |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Lore <Item>

Bards, who make careers out of recording the history and lore of
people, places, and things, can use this knowledge to good advantage
when attempting to ascertain information about an object. Along
with the more basic items of an item, the bard may occasionally
learn more about the object's history.

~




-1 SNEAK~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|       Sneak                                                         |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Sneak

The sneak skill is used to move silently. It has several visible 
affects. Firstly, when used in conjunction with the hide command
(see help HIDE), it allows someone to move without stepping out of the
shadows. Secondly, it allows objects to be taken from the room without
arosing suspicion. Finally, even for those not hiding, it allows exit
from a room to go unnoticed.

~

-1 'HERBAL MEDICINE' HERBAL~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|      Herbal Medicine                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Herbal <Target (Optional)>

Herbal medicine may be prepared by a druid as a healing aid. At higher
levels of druidical power, the medicine may also be used in an attempt
to cure poison or plague. Herbal medicine may only be concocted in the
forests.

~



-1 DEATH DYING~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|      Death                                                          |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

When your character dies, you are reincarnated back at the Altar of 
the Temple of your home city.  Your corpse is left behind in the room 
where you were killed, together with all of your equipment.

Any spells which were affecting you are cancelled by death, but 
following and groups are not affected by death.

You lose experience points for dying.  The amount you lose is dependent
on your current level.

You may also lose vitality (constitution) when you die. If you did lose
constitution, a scholar of water might be able to help you with the
ressurect spell, which has a chance to restore lost con.

Corpses decay after time, and the objects inside corpses decay with 
them. Player corpses last *roughly* 15 hours of game time (15 minutes of 
real time). After the corpses decay, your items will return to the altar
you recall to in your home town.

After your death, you will return as a ghost. You will remain a
ghost until you return to a healer in town (and use the 
'Heal Resurrect' command), or are resurrected by a water scholar.
Ghosts are automatically given pass door, flying, and the
ability to see in the dark. Ghosts are also immune to being
attacked, and cannot initiate combat or use hostile magic and
skills of any kind. Ghosts can loot possessions from their
own corpse, but are unable to take any other items.

After level 10, you must remain a ghost a minimum of five minutes
before being resurrected. After twenty minutes as a ghost, your
constitution will begin to slowly drain away. When it reaches 3,
you will perish again, this time losing a point of vitality.
This means that once your corpse has decayed to the altar, it is
always to your advantage to return to the temple.

Each time you die, there is a chance you can lose constitution.
For more info, see help CON DEATH.

~

-1 'CON DEATH' 'CONSTITUTION DEATH' 'CON LOSS' 'THE FINAL DEATH'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|        Con Death                                                    |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Whenever your character dies, there is a chance you will lose a point 
of constitution. Should your constitution ever fall below four, your
character will die permanently. After this, you will walk the lands
a brief time as a ghost. Following this period, your character will
disappear entirely, so make the most of this time to bid your final
farewells.

~

