-1 NEWBIE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|             Newbie                                                  |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/


If you're completely new to the World of Avendar, then this file is
for you.

Q: So what exactly is this place, anyway?

A: Avendar: The Crucible of Legends is a MUD set in the
fantasy world of Avendar.

Q: So what is a MUD exactly, anyway?

A: A MUD, (short for multi-user dungeon) is a simulated
world in which multiple users interact with each
other, and the world around them, in the context of their
setting.

Q: So, what is Avendar like anyway?

A: Avendar MUD features a number of things, but probably
the three most important features are:

-Avendar is its own original world, with a unique cast of
classes, people, places and ideas

-Avendar is a role-playing MUD

-Avendar is a MUD which allows for playerkilling

Q: Roleplaying MUD? What does that mean? Do I have to
dress in black and drink blood? Sacrifice babies?

A: What playing on a roleplaying MUD means is that you
take on the role of the character you assume. This means you
don't come here to discuss real life -- you come to step into
a fantasy role. And, no one says you *have* to drink blood.
For more help on this topic, read help ROLEPLAYING.

Q: Playerkilling? What's that all about?

A: On Avendar, part of your interaction with others might
involve a threat to your own well-being by other players.
Part of the reasoning for this is that you really aren't
able to role-play things like the epic struggle between
good and evil without some sort of violence. For more
help on this, read help PLAYERKILLING.

Q: Ok, well, what all sorts of things do people do here?

A: You can do lots of things here. You can go out to kill
creatures and gain experience and improve yourself, go exploring,
meet and interact with other people, or even get in a tussle
with other players. Really, the sky is the limit.

Q: If I keep playing, will Avendar devour my soul?

A: Yes.


For more help on the mechanics of getting started, read help STARTING.

~


