-1 FORM  FORMS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       FORMS                                                         |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/


A swordmaster, more than a mere warrior, has devoted his life to
the mastery of various styles, or "forms" of combat. Each
form accomplishes different goals in battle, and can and should
be used strategically. Assuming a form requires mana, and
each round of combat that a form is being used requires mana
(and sometimes stamina) to maintain that form. If you do not
have the mana to pay the cost of the form, the form will drop.
In addition, each form has a counterform, that will cause the
swordmaster to lose his stance, rendering him vulnerable to attack.
Swordmasters must be wielding a sword to assume a form.


Syntax:

Assume <form name>

Example:

Assume Form of the Bear

To drop out of your form all together, use "Assume none"

To get a complete list of forms, type FORMS.
~

