-1 BUG TYPO IDEA~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       BUG TYPO                                                      |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Should you happen to run across a bug or a typo, the first thing you
should do is pray about it.  An immortal can gain more information
through a direct conversation with you than he/she probably could
by going through a note.

If there is no response, you should write a note to immortal,
detailing the precise events that lead up to the bug.  Here
are a few things you should try and keep in mind:

-Describe exactly what you think is wrong
-In certain cases, information about your inventory, the room
you're in, what mobs are around you, and what spells you're
affected by will be necessary.  Try to think about which of
the above could possibly bring about said bug, and be sure
to list them.  Try to be as specific as possible.
-If you need to point out a specific room, be sure to give
specific instructions, especially if the room is one of many
(i.e. "The Arien Plains").
-Try not to get upset about the bug. If there's a problem, we 
want just as badly as you to fix it as soon as possible.

IMPORTANT:
The immortals consider the abuse of bugs to be among one of the
graver sins that a mortal can commit.  Do not abuse bugs, or
else you will be treated harshly.


~

-1 HP 'HIT POINTS'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|             Hit Points                                              |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Your characters hit points are a measure of your ability
to sustain physical injuries to your body. If your hit points
ever drop to 0, you become incapacitated and begin to
slowly bleed to death. If your hp drop to ^10, your character
will die. (see help DEATH) As your level increases, so 
too will your hit points. How much your hit points increase
is a function of your character's constitution and class.

~


-1 MANA~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|               Mana                                                  |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Your character's mana is an attempt to quantify mental
concentration and the ability to channel magical energy.
In general, spells will require mana to cast, as well as
some skills which require concentrated effort. As you
progress in level, so too will your mana supply. How much
your mana increases is a function of your character's intellect,
wisdom, and class. Additionally, the 'casting cost' (the
amount of mana it takes to cast a given spell) will often go
down as your character advances in level.

~

