-1 STONES 'STONE OF POWER' 'STONES OF POWER'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|             Stones of Power                                         |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Artifacts of ancient magic pre-dating the Fall of the Alatharya,
the stones of power are focii for channeling various forms
of energy. Used by the varying houses of Avendar to 
utilize the ancient forms that they have preserved, the stones
are kept by them in their vaults to channel this power. 
The more stones a house has acquired, the more powers it
can tap. House abilities are acquired in the follow manner:

Number of Powers                  Number of Stones in Vault
---------------                 ---------------------------------
1	                                    1
2	                                    2
3	                                    4
4	                                    7
5	                                    10

Stones of Power are known to have other effects, some
well-known, others obscure. They are coveted not only by
the houses that use them for their might, but by others
who know their less-popular benfits.

The nature of the stones is such that trying to leave Avendar
results in their loss, and sacrificed or otherwise destroyed 
stones slowly reassemble themselves. Stones appear in all
manner of places -- from simple city streets to the depths of
an arch-demon's prison.

Related Helps:
HOUSES VAULT
~


-1 VAULT~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|                 Vault                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Each of the houses of Avendar has a vault in which it may
places the stones of power to gain skills, store equipment
to use at a later date or to keep from falling into the hands of
the enemy. Items placed in the vault persist even through
reboots/crashes, thereby maintaing the equipment within.
Vaults all have guardians, which behave in a set manner.

The way in which a House's guardian functions is passed down
by word of mouth, in the oral tradition.

If you are raiding a house to gain access to the vault, you will
have to slay the guardian(s) of the house to obtain the magical
item that will give you access to the vault.

Related Helps: 
HOUSES 'STONE OF POWER' 
~

