-1 ATTRIBUTES STATS STATISTICS~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|      STATS                                                          |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Your statistics (stats) determine the degree of your 
character's physical, mental, and spiritual aptitudes. 
Stats range from 3-25, and are as follows

Strength: 

Your strength determines your character's brute physical
strength. High strength allows you to do more damage,
carry more things, as well as influencing skills that involve
brute force.

Intellect:

Your intelligence determines your ability to analyze and solve
problems, as well as the ability to learn and memorize facts.
Your intelligence influences a number of things, such as how
many practice sessions it takes for you to learn a skill, along
with the amount of mana your acquire at each level.


Wisdom 

Your wisdom measures your intuition, creativity, and ability to
make generalizations based on your own individual observations.
Your wisdom affects the number of practice sessions you gain
with each level, and to a small extent the amount of mana you
acquire.

Dexterity:

Your dexterity represents your speed, agility, and overall response
time. Your dexterity affects a large number of skills, along with
your armor class.

Constitution:

Constitution is a measure of your total health and vigor. Constitution
is lost with each death, and if your constituion should ever drop 
below 3, you will die. Constituion helps determine the number of
hit points you gain each level, along with how much health is restored
per hour when resting.

Charisma:

Your charisma measures not only your physical attractiveness, but also
the personality traits which tend to influence others to to seek out your
presence, ideas, and opinions. Charisma affects the workings of bard
songs, as well as a number of  other skills relating to personality
and appearance.


