-1 VOIDWALK 'VOID WALK'~

/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|             Voidwalk                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Voidwalk'

The experienced scholar of the void through long experience can
bring their own body slightly out of phase with the prime material,
and dwell briefly in the fringes of the void. While in this state, void
scholars can neither be seen nor attacked. Scholars in this state also 
exist partially outside of our plane of existence, so are unable to
interact with the physical world. Upon the termination of the spell, the 
scholar returns to the prime material, where his or her body will have
suffered the effects of prolonged contact with the void.

~


-1 POSSESSION POSESSION POSESION POSSESION~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|            Possession                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'possession' <mob>

Reaching out through the void, a scholar of the void may attempt
to insinuate his will into the mind of a creature. Successful 
possession attempts result in the scholar assuming control 
of the victim's body. The void scholar's body reminds behind,
where it remains vulnerable to physical attack. To return to their
body, a scholar uses the RELINQUISH command.

~

-1 RELINQUISH~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|          Relinquish                                                 |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Relinquish

Void scholars use the RELINQUISH command to undo
the affects of the POSSESSION spell, returning them to
their own body.

~

-1 TENTACLES~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|          Tentacles                                                  |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'tentacles'

By reaching into the plane of the void, a spellcaster may summon
forth some of the more primitive life forms that inhabit that region.
The result is a growth of black tentacles, which grab at any and all
who enter, leave, or remain in the room with them.

~


-1 LESSER 'LESSER DEMON SUMMON'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|           Lesser  Demon  Summon                                     |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Lesser Demon Summon'

One of the spells that typifies magic-users who dabble in the
powers of the void is the summoning of lesser void-dwelling 
entities, or demons. Binding them with the tenants of an ancient
agreement, lesser demons can be made to serve practitioners of
void. The aspiring demon summoner need be wary, however:
demons require a price for their service, and demand it when
summoned. Those who are unwilling or unable to pay the 
price often pay the ultimate penalty. Demons are also more
difficult to control the longer they are bound, and have been
known to break their bonds after enough time has elapsed.
To return a demon to its home plane, the BANISH spell is
used.

~



-1 'GREATER DEMON SUMMON' 'GREATER DEMON'~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|         Greater Demon Summon                                        |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Summon Greater Demon'

Similar in form to the Lesser Demon Summoning, only a master
scholar of void may attempt this spell. Used to bind demons of
near legendary status from the Void, this spell should only be
attempted with the utmost caution, as greater demons demand
exorbitant prices for their service, and are easily offended if 
their cost is denied. Like lesser demons, the BANISH spell
is used to return them to their home plane.

~


-1 BANISH~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\ 
|            Banish                                                   |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: Cast 'Banish' <Demon>

This spell attempts to return a summoned demon to the 
plane of the void, in an attempt to circumvent the demon's
eventual escape from the caster's control.

~

