Syntax: cast 'nexus' <anchor>

By achoring an endpoint to a place where the <anchor> target is,
the caster is able to tunnel through the void, and open a temporary
gateway that can be walked through. The targetting of the endpoint
follows much the same rules as the gate (help GATE) spell. This
spell is extremely taxing, and the trip through a nexus can be
disorienting.

~



-1 REQUEST~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       REQUEST                                                       |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: request <item> <requestee>

With request, a person who follows the light can ask to receive
an item from a good creature or person of the land (non-PC). You may
only request within 5 levels of yourself. If successful, and the
person you request from also walks in the light, they will entrust you
with the item, assuming that since you are asking, you have a greater
need. By requesting an item, you, a lightwalker, are removing that
persons ability to defend themselves, and should consider that
accordingly. (see also: help ROLEPLAYING)

~

