-1 AVENDAR~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       AVENDAR                                                       |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Avendar began as a hobby, unopened to the public, in September
of 1997. In November 1997, a core group of immortals left the muds they
played to dedicate their time to this project. Working all hours of
the day and night, they produced the first iteration of the world in
which you stand, which opened in January of 1998.

Avendar began as merely a derivative of Rom2.4b, originally named
"Pantheon". Now, it begins to take on life of its own. It has integrated
mob and object programs, "MobMemory" and "ObjMemory", hundreds of new
skills and spells, and entirely replaced the world once common to Rom,
with an entirely original fantasy mythos.

The development continues as Avendar is now fully in production.  
Our primary objectves are a highly interactive world, lots of originality,
and a world where roleplaying is emphasized, and anything is possible. Our
original area set is growing as we find new immortals worthy of adding
to the staff, and as we revamp older areas with our newer code
developments. Thanks for being a part of this.

The creators of Avendar wish to thank our predecessors, the
authors of DIKU, Merc, ROM; the creators and maintainors of
The Carrionfields, a progenitor of our efforts; Marc Mahoney and
Chris Papadimitriou for their early efforts, as well as Xurinos,
wherever you're at.

~


