\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: cast armor
Syntax: cast shield
Syntax: cast 'stone skin'


These spells protect the target by decreasing (improving) the caster's 
defensive ability.  ARMOR and SHIELD both improve the targets armor 
class by 20, and STONE SKIN provides a resistance to physical attacks.
~

-1 SLEEP~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       SLEEP                                                         |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: cast sleep <victim>

This spell puts its victim to sleep.
~

-1 SUMMON~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       SUMMON                                                        |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: cast summon <character>

The summon spell is used to conjure a creature from anywhere in Avendar.
Players can also be summoned, but only if they are in the same area
as the caster. Not all creatures can be summoned, and creatures of
an alignment different from the caster may have a hostile reaction.
The summoning spell requires a pentagram of summoning.
~

-1 TELEPORT~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       TELEPORT                                                      |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: cast <teleport>

This spell takes you from your current location to a random location somewhere
in the world.
~

-1 VENTRILOQUATE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       VENTRILOQUATE                                                 |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Syntax: cast ventriloquate <speaker> <message>

This spell throws your voice, making it appear that some other object or
character in the room is saying your message.  Victims who make their saving
throw will know that someone is using ventriloquism, but not who.  Victims who
fail their saving throw will think that the object or character really did say
your message.
~

