-1 LAWFUL-GOOD 'LAWFUL GOOD' LG~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       LAWFUL-GOOD LG                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons of good alignment and lawful ethos are given to the view that the 
most good comes through the rule of law. Even when they do not support
an existing regime,  they will tend to act within the existing system to enact
change rather than support social unrest.


~

-1 NEUTRAL-GOOD 'NEUTRAL GOOD' NG~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       NEUTRAL-GOOD NG                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are neutral good are unconcerned with matters of law and chaos. 
Instead, they prefer to use both law and chaos to attain the end of doing good.


~

-1 CHAOTIC-GOOD 'CHAOTIC GOOD' CG~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       CHAOTIC-GOOD CG                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are chaotic good tend to view laws or rules with supsicion, if
not outright disbelief. Holding to the view that the most good comes when
individuals are allowed to act free of impediments and the shackles of
man-made law.


~

-1 LAWFUL-NEUTRAL 'LAWFUL NEUTRAL' LN~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       LAWFUL-NEUTRAL LN                                             |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are lawful neutral tend to view rules and order as primaries.
Whatever other views they may hold, generally, order and law will be
viewed as means of attaining these goals.



~

-1 NEUTRAL-NEUTRAL 'NEUTRAL NEUTRAL' 'TRUE NEUTRAL'NN~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       NEUTRAL-NEUTRAL NN                                            |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are true neutral are completely indifferent to both moral 
and secular law.  This may manifest itself as unconcern for these issues, 
or a true concern for maintaining the balance of the world.


~

-1 CHAOTIC-NEUTRAL 'CHAOTIC NEUTRAL' CN~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       CHAOTIC-NEUTRAL CN                                            |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are chaotic neutral are known for their fickle natures. Refusing
to be bound by law, and indifferent to moral concern, they are born gamblers, 
adventurers, or general free spirits. 


~

-1 LAWFUL-EVIL 'LAWFUL EVIL' LE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       LAWFUL-EVIL LE                                                |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are lawful evil prefer to use the existing power structures of
society to advance their own ends. They are often characterized as manipulative
or scheming, using a long-term view in attaining their ends.


~

-1 NEUTRAL-EVIL 'NEUTRAL EVIL' NE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       NEUTRAL-EVIL NE                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are neutral evil are completely motivated by their own self 
interest. They will use whatever means are available at hand in order to
secure their own interests, disbarring all moral equivocation.


~

-1 CHAOTIC-EVIL 'CHAOTIC EVIL' CE~
/---------------------------------------------------------------------\
|       CHAOTIC-EVIL CE                                               |
\---------------------------------------------------------------------/

Persons who are chaotic evil draw their strength from their complete lack 
of concern for order or the law. Emphasizing their own dark version of
 individualism, they are often quite savage, and are quite willing
to commit any atrocity to accomplish their own ends.


~

